<paragraph blockId="15.[189,303,608,634]" box="[189,303,608,634]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,608,634]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,608,634]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,655,752]" lastBlockId="16.[189,1399,267,575]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Erdos" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[258,417,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phragmitis">
<emphasis box="[258,417,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">T. phragmitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has previously been reported from 
<taxonomicName box="[854,989,655,681]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[854,989,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Phragmites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Noyes J. S." box="[1067,1218,655,681]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref12166" refString="Noyes J. S. 2020. Universal Chalcidoidea Database. Natural History Museum, London. Available from https: // www. nhm. ac. uk / our-science / data / chalcidoids / database / [accessed 1 Jan. 2020]." type="url" year="2020">Noyes 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Based on the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Claridge M. F." box="[274,464,690,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="175 - 216" refId="ref11139" refString="Claridge M. F. 1961. Α contribution to the biology and taxonomy of some Palaearctic species of Tetramesa Walker (= Isosoma Walk.; = Harmolita Motsch.) (Hymenoptera: Eurytomidae) with particular reference to the British fauna. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 113: 175 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1961. tb 00807. x" type="journal article" year="1961">Claridge (1961)</bibRefCitation>
, our specimens are closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1832)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[914,1322,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[914,1135,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tetramesa cornuta</emphasis>
(Walker, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
in the couplet 17, sharing with this species the following characters: funicular segments short with F5 quadrate; pronotum transverse (
<figureCitation box="[447,557,267,293]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[286,1305,810,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[283,1305,810,1921]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 10. Tetramesa sp. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Male in lateral view. D. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011144/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
), about 2× as wide as long; mid tibial spur relatively long, longer than half length of basitarsus; longer GT3 non-emarginate posteriorly. However, the female appears to be larger than is reported for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[503,624,339,364]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[503,624,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">T. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; marginal vein at most as long as stigmal vein (vs marginal vein twice as long as stigmal vein in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[578,699,374,399]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[578,699,374,399]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">T. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); metasoma longer than the combined length of head plus mesosoma (75:65) (vs metasoma shorter than combined length of head and mesosoma in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[1260,1381,409,434]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[1260,1381,409,434]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">T. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In the male, the funicular segments are slightly longer than in the female (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1163,443,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[286,1305,810,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[283,1305,810,1921]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 10. Tetramesa sp. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Male in lateral view. D. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011144/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
) but a more distinct sexual dimorphism was observed in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[637,761,479,504]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[637,761,479,504]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">T. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Claridge M. F." box="[780,958,478,504]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="175 - 216" refId="ref11139" refString="Claridge M. F. 1961. Α contribution to the biology and taxonomy of some Palaearctic species of Tetramesa Walker (= Isosoma Walk.; = Harmolita Motsch.) (Hymenoptera: Eurytomidae) with particular reference to the British fauna. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 113: 175 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1961. tb 00807. x" type="journal article" year="1961">Claridge 1961</bibRefCitation>
: figs 97–98). This species clearly is different from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[360,479,515,540]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[360,479,515,540]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">T. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and may be new. However, further specimens are required and we also need to examine several 
<typeStatus box="[386,437,549,575]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
specimens belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1848" box="[847,968,550,575]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,968,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Tetramesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to ascertain its novelty.
</paragraph>
